rComments: I think this was his first time teaching and going to class isn't really necessary because he just reads the slides. His slides have so much information so that you could teach yourself. The tests and finals were very similar to the practice ones from previous years so as long as you practiced them you were set up for success.

Not a bad prof, but his lectures are very similar to the textbook. He posts old exams which is helpful. Exams are usually graded out of 20 marks which makes it pretty easy to get a bad grade if you mess up.

Lectures are completely useless, he basically puts the textbook in slides and reads them. He does post old midterms which is nice and if you literally only study the midterms you can get a good grade.
